== Chips ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @Potatoes{600%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm wide chips.

Pop the chips onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @Oil{to taste}, season well with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%mins}. Turn the tray halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

== Panko Crust ==

In a #bowl{}, mix the @Breadcrumbs{1%pack} with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

Pat the @Hake{250%g} and @Prawns{180%g} with #kitchen paper{} to remove excess moisture. Season with salt and pepper.

In a medium #bowl{}, toss both hake and prawns with half the @Aioli{2%sachets}.

Then, one by one, toss the hake and prawns through the breadcrumbs.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

== Baking ==

Place the crumbed hake on a lined baking tray.

Drizzle with oil and place on the middle shelf of the oven.

Bake until the crumb is golden and the fish is cooked through, ~{18-20%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

When the hake has been cooking for ~{10%mins}, add the prawns to the same tray and cook for the remaining time, ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

== Carrot Slaw ==

Meanwhile, quarter the @Lemon{1}.

Trim the @Carrot{1}, then coarsely grate (no need to peel).

Mix the carrot with two-thirds of the remaining aioli (reserve one-third for drizzling over later).

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

== Peas ==

Place a #pot{} over medium-high heat with @Butter{1%tbsp} and a drizzle of @Oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the @Peas{120%g} and cook, stirring, until warmed through, ~{2-3%mins}.

Mash the peas with a #fork{} and season to taste with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Just before serving, toss the chips with @Apple Cider Vinegar{2%sachets}, salt and pepper then divide between plates.

Serve the crumbed hake, prawns, peas, carrot slaw and lemon wedges alongside.

Drizzle the remaining aioli over the crispy fish and prawns.